	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Thomas</placeName> <date>23<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> Dec&#47;62</date></p>
				<p>Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have the pleasure to own the<lb/> receipt of your esteemed lines of <date>6<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date>. Inst&#44;<lb/> and now beg to hand you herewith a Dft.<lb/> for &#36;47.78 for collections &#38;c as p note annexed.<lb/>  The <date>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi></date> thereof was sent to <placeName>Boston</placeName> on <date>15<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> Inst.<lb/> for acceptance&#44; and will no doubt have been<lb/> forwarded you thence ere the receipt of this.<lb/>  <persName>Mrs. DaCosta</persName> being unwell since last year&#44;<lb/> her copy of the Occident has been given up&#44;<lb/> and is taken by <persName>Mr. M. D. Osorio</persName>. <persName>Rev. Myers</persName><lb/> said ere his departure that he would pay<lb/> his subscription to <persName>Mr. Nathan</persName>&#44; your Agent<lb/> in <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>.  You mention having asked me<lb/> lately to collect for the magazine&#44; but that<lb/> letter must have strayed&#44; as I did not notice<lb/> the request before.  The Bibles and Prayer Bks.<lb/> having been sold you may send me a new<lb/> supply.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You will have perceived that a Minister for<lb/> our congregation has been advertised for.  The<lb/> promptitude of the Board I believe was not gen<lb/>erally known by the members&#44; but to have the<lb/> vacancy speedily filled would&#44; doubtless meet<lb/> with the concurrence of a large number.  In<lb/> fact the Bye Laws in <sic>recognising</sic> the Minister<lb/> as one of the Officers of the Synagogue do not<lb/> provide for his absence&#44; and therefore it is held<lb/> that these laws cannot be binding on the members<lb/> while the illegality of any article can be proved.<lb/>  But I understand that only &#36;1200. have been<lb/> offered and while I know that our congregation<lb/> cannot afford a salary of &#36;2000. as you suggest&#44;<lb/> its expenses being already large&#44; I must likewise<lb/> confess that less than &#36;1500. would be very small.<lb/>  I would mention privately that there is now<lb/> an application but of course the candidate is<lb/> not an Englishman&#44; and it is not known whether<lb/> he has had much practice in English oratory.<lb/>  In many other respects he would suit us&#44; and</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>therefore&#44; if this and one or two other points of<lb/> which I wrote you before&#44; can be satisfactorily<lb/> understood and arranged&#44; it is not improbable<lb/> that we will soon secure his services.  I have<lb/> <sic>shewn</sic> your letter to one or two of my acquain<lb/>tances whom I know to be favorable to your<lb/> views&#59; but in no community&#44; I believe&#44; are all<lb/> the members thereof found to agree on any sub<lb/>ject&#44; and the causes which led to the resigna<lb/>tion of our former Minsters have therefore been<lb/> beyond the control of our congregation</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With regard&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I am&#44; Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Yours&#44; truly&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">David M. Pizal</persName></p>
				<p>P. S. I did not collect<lb/> from <persName>Mr. Simmonds</persName><lb/> as you made no mention of it.</p>
				<p>Rec&#39;d for Occident from <persName>Major Wolff</persName>&#44;</p>
				<p><persName>Messrs. J. Fidanque Jr</persName>&#44; <persName>Sol. L. Maduro</persName>&#44;</p>
				<p><persName>M. R. A. Correa</persName>&#44; <persName>A. D. DeJongh&#44; M. D.</persName></p>
				<p><persName>Osorio</persName>&#44; &#38; self&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#36;21.&#8212;</p>
				<p>4 D. Prayers &#36;12 4 Bibles &#36;10&#160;&#160;<hi rend="underline">22</hi></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"> &#36;43.&#8212;</p>
				<p>Dft &#64; 10 D&#47;S on <persName>W. J. Haskell &#38; Co.</persName> <placeName>Boston</placeName> &#36;47.78&#64;10&#37; dis. <hi rend="underline">43</hi></p>
